com.exlibris.dps.sdk.techmd

Interface MDExtractorPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    TechnicalMDExtractorPlugin

    public interface MDExtractorPlugin
extends TechnicalMDExtractorPlugin

    Interface for metadata extractors. Each extractor handles a specific format and extracts its attributes.
    This plugin interface only supports java implementation.

    • Method Detail

      • getProfile

        default java.lang.String getProfile()
        Extracts a file's attributes according to the given file path. Extraction of all attributes relevant to the format implementation.
        The attribute values can be given using the getAttributeByName(String) method
        Parameters:
        file - the file path to extract
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if an unexpected exception occurs, such as IOException.

      • getImageCount

        java.lang.Integer getImageCount()
        This method is relevant only for image extractors. Returns the number of images if the file (such as TIFF, JPEG, etc.) contains several pages/images
        Returns:
        the number of images that are part of the full image in the case of a complex image.

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Implementation of a general file validation. If there is no specific implementation, return true.
        Returns:
        validation result if implemented, otherwise true.

      • isWellFormed

        boolean isWellFormed()

        file formed result if implemented, otherwise true.
